	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Residents have been evacuated from a building in Johannesburg's CBD after a fire broke out on the first floor on Thursday afternoon, emergency services told News24. The fire has since been extinguished. The building is on corner of De Villiers and Rissik street. Emergency services spokesperson Nana Radebe confirmed that there were no fatalities. “For now, we are not sure what caused the fire but have managed to evacuate everyone. We will do the final search to ensure that no one was left inside.,” she said. #JoburgFire We're on scene of a structural fire at Cnr Rissik & De Villiers in the Joburg CBD, pls avoid the area. The fire has been contained, some occupants of the building have been taken out safely, firefighters currently conducting further search & rescue.Pic via @Adolph_89 pic.twitter.com/CTmmzIt9uT — City of Joburg EMS (@CityofJoburgEMS) August 16, 2018 #RissikStreet. @CityofJoburgZA people trapped in the building and its not clear how many people pic.twitter.com/xnxzdIJyBe — #AdolphTurns29?????? (@Adolph_89) August 16, 2018  She said emergency services were alerted to the blaze around 14:00 and dispatched three fire trucks to the scene. Radebe said firefighters managed to prevent the fire from spreading to other floors of the building. She added that preliminary investigations would be conducted to establish what caused the blaze. More to follow. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  